  "texts": [
    "Bold error bars (95% CI) show whether overall effect size is significantly different from zero (i.e.",
    "not overlapping zero), while light error bars show the 95% prediction interval (PI) of effect sizes, and black dot shows mean effect size.",
    "Sample sizes reported as: k = number of effect sizes (in brackets: number of studies).",
    "Source data is provided as a source data file.",
    "Fig. 16A)."
  ]
